{
  "title": "ISic001626. Epitaph for Sokrates",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo, Alex Antoniou</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σωκράτης\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σωκράτης\"><span data-text=\"Σωκράτης\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Σωκράτης\">Σωκράτης</span></span></span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>☧ <span data-text=\"πάντων\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"πᾶς\">πάντων</span>  <span data-text=\"ὁ\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"ὁ\">ὁ</span> ☧ <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"φίλος\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"φίλος\">φίλος</span>  <span data-text=\"ἐνθά\n                    δε\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"ἐνθάδε\">ἐνθά-<br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span>δε</span>  <span data-text=\"κεῖται\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"κεῖμαι\">κεῖται</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Victoria Fendel, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive-simple-lemmatized\">  <div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <span data-text=\"Σωκράτης\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Σωκράτης\">Σωκράτης</span>  <span data-text=\"πάντων\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"πᾶς\">πάντων</span>  <span data-text=\"ὁ\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"ὁ\">ὁ</span>  <span data-text=\"φίλος\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"φίλος\">φίλος</span>  <span data-text=\"ἐνθάδε\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"ἐνθάδε\">ἐνθάδε</span>  <span data-text=\"κεῖται\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"κεῖμαι\">κεῖται</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo, Alex Antoniou</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σωκράτης\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σωκράτης\"><span data-text=\"Σωκράτης\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Σωκράτης\">ΣΩΚΡΑΤΗΣ</span></span></span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>☧<span data-text=\"πάντων\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"πᾶς\">ΠΑΝΤΩΝ</span><span data-text=\"ὁ\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"ὁ\">Ο</span>☧<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"φίλος\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"φίλος\">ΦΙΛΟΣ</span><span data-text=\"ἐνθά\n                    δε\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"ἐνθάδε\">ΕΝΘΑ<br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span>ΔΕ</span><span data-text=\"κεῖται\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"κεῖμαι\">ΚΕΙΤΑΙ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Victoria Fendel, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\"><div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><span data-text=\"Σωκράτης\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Σωκράτης\">ΣΩΚΡΑΤΗΣ</span><span data-text=\"πάντων\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"πᾶς\">ΠΑΝΤΩΝ</span><span data-text=\"ὁ\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"ὁ\">Ο</span><span data-text=\"φίλος\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"φίλος\">ΦΙΛΟΣ</span><span data-text=\"ἐνθάδε\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"ἐνθάδε\">ΕΝΘΑΔΕ</span><span data-text=\"κεῖται\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"κεῖμαι\">ΚΕΙΤΑΙ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic001626_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001626_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001626.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001626-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text based on photograph</span>  </span>; </li><li><span class=\"line 2\">line.2: <span>Orsi, Agnello, Wessel: πάντων ὁ | φίλος; Ferrua, Korhonen: πάντων | φίλος (Ο is part of the Christogram)</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>Sokrates, the friend of all, lies here.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>Italian translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo</a></p>  <p>Sokrates, l’amico di tutti, giace qui.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>This epitaph has a formula very similar to pagan epitaphs, although the presence of the two Christograms denotes it as Christian. Ferrua and Korhonen read <span class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">πάντων φίλος</span> with the interpretation of <span class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ο</span> as part of the Christogram, which in this case should be interpreted as <span class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ὁ Χ(ριστό)ς</span> (the same hight of the letter <span class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">O</span> compared to the other letters of the text is probably a misinterpretation of the stonecutter). However, there is no need to eliminate the article since other parallels of similar epithets denoting friendship and affection in Christian inscriptions, such as IMusCatania 178 = <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001359\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001359</a> and SEG 65. 791 = <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001633\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001633</a> present the names of the deceased followed by adjectives preceded by the article (<span class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Κάλλιστος καὶ | Εὐκαρπία οἱ φιλόστορ|γοι</span> and <span class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ὁ πανφίλ|ητος ... Εὐδέμων</span> respectively).</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 1022 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000394\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000394</a>  </li><li> Orsi NSA 1918 62 no.3 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392</a>  </li><li> Agnello 1953 no.58) <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002211\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002211</a>  </li><li> Ferrua 1989 110 no.416 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995</a>  </li><li> Korhonen 2004 196 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Regular letters with apices, lunate Ε and Σ, cursive Ω, A, Δ and Λ with extended serifs. Two Christograms at l. 2.</p> Lines 1-4  33-45  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not recorded  </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
